Quote:  <i> whio </i>, a water-bird (Hymenolaimus malacorhynchus), blue-duck, mountain-duck, whistling duck; name echoic, like English whew-duck having a similar name for the same reason. The place-name Whiorau, means blue-ducks a-plenty.
Notes:  Andersen Maori Words in English

